sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45905
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Composite part for fluorescent detection of botulinum neurotoxin A (BoNT A)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Human neurotransmitter coding sequence (SNAP-25) targeted by botulinum neurotoxin A (BoNT) with green fluorescent protein (GFP) reporter and histadine tag for adhesion.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aaron Fronk
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: SNAP-25: Homo sapiens GFP: Aequorea victoria
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Optimized for expression in E. coli

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45904
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The section of the human neurotransmitter protein SNAP-25 required for binding and cleavage by the botulinum neurotoxin A (BoNT), according to the findings of Vaidyanathan et al. (2002).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Aaron Fronk
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence is optimized for expression in E. coli.

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Point mutation to make it RFC compatible
